The traditions and the name of the interreges point to the kingly period of Rome, and the vacancy at the death of the elective monarch, when there was no successor to step at once into his place. Then, says Livy 1. 17. 4‚the senate divided itself into ten decuriae, in each oi which the lot decided the order of rank. A board consisting of one of each decuria then held the monarchy in commission for 50 days, each in turn bearing the insignia of supreme command for 5.
